sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K773002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part carries the gene for a proteorhodopsin pump, which can generate a proton motive force for making ATP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We codon optimized the gene for E. coli and eliminated four restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Katie Knister

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1123010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The DNA sequence for this part was obtained from the article holding the information about the FNR promotor we used: "Transcription Regulation by Tandem-Bound FNR at E.coli Promoters" by Bernard et al.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part holds the DNA sequence for the ribosoom binding site used in the large constructs by the TU-Eindhoven team in 2013. The RBS site was placed behind a FNR promoter sequence and was used to express a number of different proteins in anaerobic conditions. The protein sequence was placed immediately behind the RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We did not adapt the protein DNA sequence in any way.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ardjan van der Linden

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1604019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of uncultered cluster bacteria SAR86 was synthetized and codon optimized by GeneScript
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains RBS and blh gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Veronica Pinamonti

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
